    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This framework describes a practical methodology for measuring end- to-end TCP Throughput in a managed IP network.  The goal is to provide a better indication in regard to user experience.  In this framework, TCP and IP parameters are specified to optimize TCP Throughput.  This document is not an Internet Standards Track specification; it is published for informational purposes.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
